{"title_page": "Beaconsfield, Western Australia", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2014}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=March 2014}}\n{{Infobox Australian place | type=suburb\n| name = Beaconsfield\n| city = [[Perth, Western Australia|Perth]]\n| state = wa\n| image = \n| caption = \n| lga = [[City of Fremantle]]\n| alternative_location_map = Australia Western Australia metropolitan Perth\n| coordinates = {{coord|32.070|S|115.764|E|display=inline,title}}\n| postcode = 6162\n| est = \n| pop = 4,120| pop_year = {{CensusAU|2006}}\n| pop_footnotes = <ref name=abs>{{Census 2006 AUS|id=SSC51111|name=Beaconsfield (State Suburb)|quick=on|accessdate=2008-10-05}}</ref>\n| area = \n| stategov = [[Electoral district of Fremantle|Fremantle]]\n| fedgov = [[Division of Fremantle|Fremantle]]\n| near-nw = [[Fremantle (suburb)|Fremantle]]\n| near-n = [[White Gum Valley, Western Australia|White Gum Valley]]\n| near-ne = [[Hilton, Western Australia|Hilton]]\n| near-w = [[South Fremantle, Western Australia|South Fremantle]]\n| near-e = [[Hilton, Western Australia|Hilton]]\n| near-sw = [[South Fremantle, Western Australia|South Fremantle]]\n| near-s = [[Hamilton Hill, Western Australia|Hamilton]]\n| near-se = [[Hamilton Hill, Western Australia|Hamilton Hill]]\n}}\n'''Beaconsfield''' is a suburb of [[Perth, Western Australia]], located within the [[City of Fremantle]]. Named after a property known as \u2018Beaconsfield\u2019 located in the area in the\n1880s, the name was officially adopted from the post office on 1 August 1894.\nThe origin is unknown, but the suburb is probably named after the town in\nEngland or the [[Earl of Beaconsfield]], [[Benjamin Disraeli]], a former [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]] [[Prime Minister of the United Kingdom]].\n\nBeaconsfield is predominantly a low to medium density residential suburb with extensive community facilities including Fremantle College, various primary schools, open space recreation reserves and local shops.\n\n==Public Spaces=\n\nDick Lawrence Oval\n\nKen Allen Field\n\nClubs\n\nShepherd St Bowling Club(Hilton Park) \n\n===Transport facilities===\n*Bus routes available\n*www.transperth.wa.gov.au\n\n==Notable citizens==\n* [[Peter Tagliaferri]], a former mayor of the [[City of Fremantle]] between 2001 and 2009<ref>{{cite news |title=On my bedside table |work=The West Australian |page=26 (''West Weekend Magazine'') |date=26 January 2008 |quote=Mr Tagliaferri lives in Beaconsfield, with his wife Albina, two teenage daughters, Liana and Georgina, and a St Bernard dog called Revlon. }}</ref>\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery>\nImage:WTF Charlie's Team Christ the King Church.jpeg|Christ the King Catholic Church\nImage:WTF Jim Owens Winterfold PS mural.jpg|Aboriginal mural at Winterfold Primary School\nImage:WTF Jim Owens St Pauls Anglican Church 4.jpg|View alongside of St Paul's Anglican Church\nImage:WTF Jim Owens Beaconsfield PS murals 1.jpg|Murals at Beaconsfield Primary School\nImage:WTF Jim Owens Beaconsfield houses 2.jpg|House under construction on Moran Street\n</gallery>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{commons-cat-inline}}\n\n{{City of Fremantle suburbs}}\n\n[[Category:Suburbs of Perth, Western Australia]]\n[[Category:Suburbs in the City of Fremantle]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2014}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=March 2014}}\n{{Infobox Australian place | type=suburb\n| name = Beaconsfield\n| city = [[Perth, Western Australia|Perth]]\n| state = wa\n| image = \n| caption = \n| lga = [[City of Fremantle]]\n| alternative_location_map = Australia Western Australia metropolitan Perth\n| coordinates = {{coord|32.070|S|115.764|E|display=inline,title}}\n| postcode = 6162\n| est = \n| pop = 4,120| pop_year = {{CensusAU|2006}}\n| pop_footnotes = <ref name=abs>{{Census 2006 AUS|id=SSC51111|name=Beaconsfield (State Suburb)|quick=on|accessdate=2008-10-05}}</ref>\n| area = \n| stategov = [[Electoral district of Fremantle|Fremantle]]\n| fedgov = [[Division of Fremantle|Fremantle]]\n| near-nw = [[Fremantle (suburb)|Fremantle]]\n| near-n = [[White Gum Valley, Western Australia|White Gum Valley]]\n| near-ne = [[Hilton, Western Australia|Hilton]]\n| near-w = [[South Fremantle, Western Australia|South Fremantle]]\n| near-e = [[Hilton, Western Australia|Hilton]]\n| near-sw = [[South Fremantle, Western Australia|South Fremantle]]\n| near-s = [[Hamilton Hill, Western Australia|Hamilton]]\n| near-se = [[Hamilton Hill, Western Australia|Hamilton Hill]]\n}}\n'''Beaconsfield''' is a suburb of [[Perth, Western Australia]], located within the [[City of Fremantle]]. Named after a property known as \u2018Beaconsfield\u2019 located in the area in the\n1880s, the name was officially adopted from the post office on 1 August 1894.\nThe origin is unknown, but the suburb is probably named after the town in\nEngland or the [[Earl of Beaconsfield]], [[Benjamin Disraeli]], a former [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]] [[Prime Minister of the United Kingdom]].\n\nBeaconsfield is predominantly a low to medium density residential suburb with extensive community facilities including Fremantle College, Challenger TAFE, primary schools, open space recreation reserves and local shops.\n\n==Facilities and amenities==\nThere are a number of schools in the suburb, including primary, high school and a technical college (Challenger TAFE) where hospitality and other courses are run. There is a restaurant at the TAFE where the food is cooked and served by the students, as are student-made cocktails.\n\n===Parks and playgrounds===\n*Beacy Park\n*Davis Park\n*Dick Lawrence Oval\n*Hilton park Soccer Fields\n*Ken Allen Field\n*James Moore Pioneer Park\n*Bruce Lee Reserve\n\n===Transport facilities===\n*Bus routes available include 98, 99, 103, 107, 140, 150, 160, 511, 513, 520, 522, 530, 531, 532, 533, 825, 881, 920, 940\n*www.transperth.wa.gov.au\n\n===Schools and education===\n*Beaconsfield Pre-Primary & PS\n*Winterfold Pre-Primary & PS [http://www.winterfoldps.wa.edu.au Winterfold PS Website]\n*[http://www.ctk.wa.edu.au Christ the King Pre-School & PS]\n*Fremantle College\n*Challenger TAFE\n*Fremantle Peel District Education\n\n===Sporting clubs===\n*Hilton Park Junior Cricket Club \n*Hilton Park Bowling & Recreation Club\n*Fremantle City Dockers Junior Football Club Inc.\n*Fremantle Roosters Rugby League Football Club Inc\n*Excalibur Fencing Club\n\n===Shops and shopping centre===\n*Lefroy Road Shopping Centre\n\n==Notable citizens==\n* [[Peter Tagliaferri]], a former mayor of the [[City of Fremantle]] between 2001 and 2009<ref>{{cite news |title=On my bedside table |work=The West Australian |page=26 (''West Weekend Magazine'') |date=26 January 2008 |quote=Mr Tagliaferri lives in Beaconsfield, with his wife Albina, two teenage daughters, Liana and Georgina, and a St Bernard dog called Revlon. }}</ref>\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery>\nImage:WTF Charlie's Team Christ the King Church.jpeg|Christ the King Catholic Church\nImage:WTF Jim Owens Winterfold PS mural.jpg|Aboriginal mural at Winterfold Primary School\nImage:WTF Jim Owens St Pauls Anglican Church 4.jpg|View alongside of St Paul's Anglican Church\nImage:WTF Jim Owens Beaconsfield PS murals 1.jpg|Murals at Beaconsfield Primary School\nImage:WTF Jim Owens Beaconsfield houses 2.jpg|House under construction on Moran Street\n</gallery>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{commons-cat-inline}}\n\n{{City of Fremantle suburbs}}\n\n[[Category:Suburbs of Perth, Western Australia]]\n[[Category:Suburbs in the City of Fremantle]]\n", "name_user": "1.126.107.159", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200e=Public Spaces:redundant info)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beaconsfield,_Western_Australia"}
